	<sect1>
		<title>Welcome to the Saxon XSLT Processor*</title>
		<para>This local service provides an XSLT Transformation Engine for transforming XML-encoded source documents using a supplied XSLT stylesheet. The service functions as a java servlet and can be invoked usingthe following syntax:</para>
		<blockquote>
			<para>
				<emphasis role="bold">http://&lsqb;hostname&rsqb;:&lsqb;port-number&rsqb;/saxon/SaxonServlet?source&equals;&lsqb;xml-source&rsqb;&amp;style&equals;&lsqb;xsl-stylesheet&rsqb;&amp;clear-stylesheet-cache&equals;yes</emphasis>
			</para>
		</blockquote>
		<para>Where:</para>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>&lsqb;hostname&rsqb; - The hostname of the Fedora server; default is localhost.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>&lsqb;port-number&rsqb; - The port number on which the Fedora server is running; default 8080.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>&lsqb;xml-source&rsqb; - The URL of the XML source file.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>&lsqb;xsl-stylesheet&rsqb; - The URL of the XSLT stylesheet file.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>clear-stylesheet-cache - An optional parameter indicating if the stylesheet cache is to be cleared. A value of of "yes" signals to clear the stylesheet cache. If the parameter is omitted or has any other value, the stylesheet cache remains untouched.</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		<para>Example:</para>
		<blockquote>
			<para>http://localhost:8080/saxon/SaxonServlet?source&equals;http://dl.lib.virginia.edu/data/xmltext/ead/viu03270&amp;style&equals;http://dl.lib.virginia.edu/bin/ead/xsl/document.xsl</para>
		</blockquote>
		<para>
			<emphasis>* This service uses the SAXON XSLT Processor from Michael Kay which is licensed under the Mozilla Public License (<ulink url="http://www.mozilla.org/MPL/">MPL</ulink>). For additonal information regarding the SAXON XSLT Processor, please refer to the Saxon project web site on SourceForge at: <ulink url="http://saxon.sourceforge.net/">http://saxon.sourceforge.net/</ulink>.</emphasis>
		</para>
	</sect1>
